{
  "texts": [
    "The term H(b) is treated as a usual MHD term, except that the update of the magnetic field components is carried out using all the information available at the moment.",
    "The following steps are preformed in the HDS scheme,",
    "where t Hall is the time step imposed by the Hall term, t Hall = 2/ √ 27 min(x 2, y 2, z 2)/η H (O'Sullivan and Downes, 2007).",
    "The HDS operator advances in time by repeating the calculation of Eqs.",
    "67 N HDS times, so that t HDS = N HDS t Hall."
  ]
}